sub_title: Senior Lecturer Bioinformatics / Data Science for Life Sciences at Hanzehogeschool Groningen / Hanze University of Applied Sciences Groningen
summary:
Pharmaceutical scientist and computational chemist, rooted in medicinal chemistry and neuropharmacology and having a doctorate in the Natural Sciences (Molecular Dynamics). 
A strong interest in the biomolecular processes involved in protein-protein and protein-ligand interactions. 
Familiar with programming in several languages and affinity with statistical methods as well as management and law issues (mainly relating to higher education, HRM, and corporations).

Command of Dutch (native), Frisian (native), English (fluent), German (reasonable), French (moderate)

Specialties: Molecular Dynamics
Medicinal Chemistry
Neuropharmacology
Statistics
Interdisciplinary projects
Intercultural communication
